## Swagger / OpenAPI Documentation Standards

Use the published `SWAGGER_DOCUMENTATION_STANDARDS.md` (same content summarized here) for all services (auth, admin, bff, future services).

### Folder structure for docs

```
src/
├── modules/
│   ├── <module>/
│   │   ├── <module>.controller.ts
│   │   ├── <module>.service.ts
│   │   ├── <module>.module.ts
│   │   ├── dto/
│   │   │   ├── <entity>.dto.ts          # Plain DTOs (validation only)
│   │   │   ├── <request>.dto.ts
│   │   │   ├── <response>.dto.ts
│   │   │   └── docs/
│   │   │       ├── <entity>.dto.docs.ts # Documented DTOs with @ApiProperty
│   │   │       ├── <request>.dto.docs.ts
│   │   │       └── <response>.dto.docs.ts
│   │   └── docs/
│   │       ├── <module>.swagger.ts      # Endpoint decorators
│   │       └── <module>.tags.ts         # Tag decorator
└── docs/
    ├── swagger.config.ts                # Global config
    └── swagger.setup.ts                 # Bootstrap setup
```

### Rules

- **No inline Swagger in controllers.** Use custom decorators from `<module>.swagger.ts` and tag decorator from `<module>.tags.ts`.
- **DTO split:** Plain DTOs (`.dto.ts`) for validation; documented DTOs (`.dto.docs.ts`) for Swagger with full `@ApiProperty` (description, example, type, required/enum/isArray as needed).
- **Status codes:** Document all relevant codes (200/201/204/400/401/403/404/409/422/500).
- **Tags:** One tag decorator per module; use lower-case plural (`users`, `blogs`, `help-desk`).
- **Global setup:** Swagger config in `docs/swagger.config.ts`; setup in `docs/swagger.setup.ts`; expose at `/docs`.
- **Versioning:** Controllers use `version: '1'` (or `['1','2']` for multi-version).
- **Examples:** Provide realistic examples in `@ApiProperty`.
- **Nested/arrays/enums:** Always declare `type`, `isArray`, and `enum`/`enumName` where applicable.

### Controller pattern

```typescript
@UsersApiTag()
@Controller({ path: "users", version: "1" })
export class UsersController {
  constructor(private readonly usersService: UsersService) {}

  @ApiCreateUser()
  @Post()
  createUser(@Body() body: CreateUserDtoDocs) {
    return this.usersService.create(body);
  }
}
```

### Common mistakes to avoid

- ❌ Inline `@ApiOperation` / `@ApiResponse` with schemas in controllers.
- ❌ Missing `@ApiProperty` in documented DTOs.
- ❌ Mixing plain and documented DTOs in the same file.

### Checklist (per PR)

- DTOs split into plain + docs; all doc properties have `@ApiProperty`.
- Controllers use custom decorators and tag decorators; no inline Swagger.
- Status codes documented; examples realistic; types/enums/arrays explicit.
- Folder structure followed; Swagger config updated with new tags when modules are added.
